@eolivelli I'd say tests are not 100% required since this does not add a new functionality or behavior and the tags are purely informative at this point. 

It would be nice to have at least basic validation, at least to ensure that it will not be broken later, but it can certainly be done in a different PR. 

As to where to look into, we have a `PulsarMockBookKeeper` and `PulsarMockLedgerHandle` which will probably need to be adjusted to also keep track of the ledger custom properties.

Thanks for the pointers. Just wanting to confirm, is it the community version or the licensed version?

Also, I did some work on ```PersistentTopicsTest``` and attempted to add a new test.
Here's basically what it did:
```
    	final String nonPartitionTopic = "nonPartitionedTopic";
    	persistentTopics.createSubscription(testTenant, testNamespace, nonPartitionTopic, "test", true, (MessageIdImpl) MessageId.latest);
    	List<String> subscriptions =  persistentTopics.getSubscriptions(testTenant, testNamespace, nonPartitionTopic + "-partition-0", true);
        Assert.assertTrue(subscriptions.contains("test"));
        persistentTopics.deleteSubscription(testTenant, testNamespace, nonPartitionTopic, "test", true);
        subscriptions =  persistentTopics.getSubscriptions(testTenant, testNamespace, nonPartitionTopic + "-partition-0", true);
        Assert.assertTrue(subscriptions.isEmpty());  
```
I also modified the config value i.e. ```pulsar.getConfiguration().setAllowAutoTopicCreation(false)```

WDYT of this?

@nkurihar *fencing* means there are other brokers taking over the ownership of topics. those brokers which took over the ownership has opened the topics and fenced the old ledgers. 

by looking into the description here, it seems to be *reasonable* to me. I think it is somehow related to zookeeper session expired. when zookeeper session expired happened, the load manager has discovered the broker disappeared from zookeeper and topic bundles are re-assigned to other brokers, those brokers fenced the topics, hence the original broker will see LedgerFencedException and Producer will fail to create. 

I think the exception should be self-recovered. did it self-recover? @nkurihar

jetty was upgraded to 9.4 a while back to get around thread pooling issues.
Looks like jquery is the last thing that needs upgrade. 
@merlimat I assume you only upgraded master, we should upgrade on other live branches too.
